properties.headline: Winter Storm Warning issued January 29 at 3:18PM AKST until January 30 at 9:00PM AKST by NWS Juneau AK
properties.description:
* WHAT...Heavy snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 6 to 9
inches. Winds gusting as high as 60 mph.

* WHERE...Haines Borough and Lynn Canal.

* WHEN...From 3 AM to 9 PM AKST Thursday.

* IMPACTS...Travel could be very difficult. Strong winds could
cause tree damage and power outages. Improperly moored boats and
aircraft may break loose from their tie-downs.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Heavy snow is likely during the late
morning and early afternoon hours. Snowfall rates of 2 inches
per hour are possible for a short time. Winds will increase
rapidly during the afternoon out of the southeast with gusts as
high as 60 mph leading to blowing and drifting snow.
properties.instruction:
If you must travel, keep an extra flashlight, food, and water in
your vehicle in case of an emergency.

For the latest road conditions call 5 1 1 or visit
511.alaska.gov.

NWSheadline: WINTER STORM WARNING IN EFFECT FROM 3 AM TO 9 PM AKST THURSDAY NEAR HAINES AND THE HAINES HIGHWAY
